From 1ab2287c7f7af44ad6bb8588865e54c2e759efed Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: StanleyYP Wang <StanleyYP.Wang@mediatek.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Mar 2026 11:27:52 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] mtk: hostapd: fix uninitialized channel in background radar

When the regulatory domain is ETSI and hostapd has restarted due to
either a crash or being killed by the user, then there is a chance
that the AP will use an uninitialized background radar channel.
Therefore, initialize the background radar channel to -1 in
hostapd_handle_dfs.

Signed-off-by: StanleyYP Wang <StanleyYP.Wang@mediatek.com>
---
 src/ap/dfs.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/ap/dfs.c b/src/ap/dfs.c
index c2780ee47..07a592a8e 100644
--- a/src/ap/dfs.c
+++ b/src/ap/dfs.c
@@ -894,6 +894,7 @@ int hostapd_handle_dfs(struct hostapd_iface *iface)
 	}
 
 	iface->cac_started = 0;
+	iface->radar_background.channel = -1;
 
 	do {
 		/* Get start (first) channel for current configuration */
-- 
2.45.2

